  "local_port": 57188,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you find \"coming soon\" projects on Kickstarter and Indiegogo?",
  "response": "Discovering \"coming soon\" projects on **Kickstarter** and **Indiegogo** allows you to stay ahead of innovative ideas and support projects even before they officially launch. While both platforms focus primarily on actively funded projects, there are several strategies you can employ to find upcoming or pre-launch campaigns. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you navigate both platforms effectively:\n\n---\n\n### **Kickstarter**\n\nKickstarter doesn\u2019t have an explicit \"coming soon\" section, but you can still discover upcoming projects through various methods:\n\n1. **Follow Your Favorite Creators:**\n   - **How:** Navigate to a creator\u2019s profile and click the \"Follow\" button.\n   - **Benefit:** You'll receive notifications when they launch new projects, allowing you to support them early.\n\n2. **Subscribe to Kickstarter Newsletters and Blogs:**\n   - **How:** Sign up for Kickstarter\u2019s newsletters or regularly check their [**Newsroom**](https://www.kickstarter.com/blog).\n   - **Benefit:** Stay informed about featured projects, upcoming launches, and platform updates.\n\n3. **Leverage Social Media:**\n   - **How:** Follow Kickstarter\u2019s official accounts on platforms like [**Twitter**](https://twitter.com/kickstarter), [**Facebook**](https://www.facebook.com/Kickstarter), and [**Instagram**](https://www.instagram.com/kickstarter/).\n   - **Benefit:** Receive real-time updates and sneak peeks into projects before they go live.\n\n4. **Use Third-Party Tools and Websites:**\n   - **Examples:** [**Kicktraq**](https://www.kicktraq.com/) provides analytics and tracking for upcoming and live Kickstarter projects.\n   - **Benefit:** Gain insights into trending projects and discover new campaigns based on data-driven recommendations.\n\n5. **Engage with the Kickstarter Community:**\n   - **How:** Participate in forums, Reddit communities like [**r/kickstarter**](https://www.reddit.com/r/kickstarter/), or other online groups.\n   - **Benefit:** Share information with fellow enthusiasts about upcoming projects and get insider tips.\n\n6. **Monitor Creator Announcements:**\n   - **How:** Follow creators on their personal websites or social media channels where they might announce upcoming Kickstarter launches.\n   - **Benefit:** Get direct updates from creators before they list their projects on Kickstarter.\n\n---\n\n### **Indiegogo**\n\nIndiegogo offers more structured ways to find upcoming or pre-launch projects compared to Kickstarter:\n\n1. **Utilize the Waiting Room Feature:**\n   - **What It Is:** Indiegogo\u2019s **Waiting Room** allows creators to gather support and pledges before their campaign officially launches.\n   - **How to Access:**\n     - Visit the [**Indiegogo Waiting Room**](https://waitingroom.indiegogo.com/) page.\n     - Browse through projects listed there that are in the pre-launch phase.\n   - **Benefit:** Secure early pledges and show support, helping creators gain momentum before the official campaign.\n\n2. **Follow and Subscribe to Indiegogo Newsletters:**\n   - **How:** Sign up for Indiegogo\u2019s newsletters to receive updates on upcoming campaigns and featured projects.\n   - **Benefit:** Get curated lists of new and upcoming projects delivered straight to your inbox.\n\n3. **Engage with Indiegogo\u2019s Blog and News Sections:**\n   - **How:** Regularly check the [**Indiegogo Blog**](https://medium.com/indiegogo) or news sections for announcements about new campaigns.\n   - **Benefit:** Stay informed about trends, success stories, and upcoming launches.\n\n4. **Leverage Social Media Channels:**\n   - **How:** Follow Indiegogo\u2019s official accounts on platforms like [**Twitter**](https://twitter.com/indiegogo), [**Facebook**](https://www.facebook.com/indiegogo), and [**LinkedIn**](https://www.linkedin.com/company/indiegogo/).\n   - **Benefit:** Receive real-time updates and discover projects that are gearing up for launch.\n\n5. **Explore Indiegogo\u2019s \"Featured\" and \"Trending\" Sections:**\n   - **How:** Navigate to the [**Featured Projects**](https://www.indiegogo.com/explore/featured) or [**Trending**](https://www.indiegogo.com/explore/trending) sections to find new and upcoming campaigns.\n   - **Benefit:** Quickly identify popular or highly anticipated projects.\n\n6. **Follow Your Favorite Creators:**\n   - **How:** Like and follow creators on Indiegogo to receive notifications about their new and upcoming projects.\n   - **Benefit:** Ensure you\u2019re among the first to know when creators launch new campaigns.\n\n7. **Participate in Indiegogo Communities and Forums:**\n   - **How:** Join online forums, Reddit communities like [**r/indiegogo**](https://www.reddit.com/r/indiegogo/), or other social groups centered around crowdfunding.\n   - **Benefit:** Share insights and learn about upcoming projects through community interactions.\n\n8. **Use Third-Party Aggregator Tools:**\n   - **Examples:** Websites like [**BackerKit**](https://www.backerkit.com/) or [**Crowdfunding Tracker**](https://www.crowdfundingtracker.com/) can provide information on upcoming Indiegogo campaigns.\n   - **Benefit:** Access a broader range of data and discover projects across multiple platforms.\n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips for Both Platforms**\n\n- **Set Up Alerts:** Use Google Alerts or similar services to get notified about new projects based on keywords related to your interests.\n  \n- **Engage with Content:** Regularly interacting with content related to your interests on both platforms can help their algorithms suggest relevant upcoming projects.\n  \n- **Network with Creators:** Building relationships with creators can give you insider information about project launches and exclusive pre-launch opportunities.\n\n- **Attend Virtual Events and Webinars:** Both Kickstarter and Indiegogo occasionally host events where upcoming projects are showcased.\n\n---\n\nBy actively engaging with both **Kickstarter** and **Indiegogo** through the methods outlined above, you can effectively discover and support \"coming soon\" projects that align with your interests. Staying proactive and involved in the crowdfunding community will enhance your ability to find and back innovative projects from the very beginning.",
